HEADWORD: Patavinity
<hw>Pat`a*vin"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>patavinitas</ets>, fr. <ets>Patavium</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>patavinit⟦eacute⟧</ets>]</ety> <def>The use of local or provincial
words, as in the peculiar style or diction of Livy, the Roman historian;
-- so called from Patavium, now Padua, the place of Livy's
nativity.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

